TITLE: Cyprus reportedly discovers a Covid variant that combines omicron and delta
SUMMARY: The strain is being called "deltacron."

TITLE: Biden administration says 'no firm commitment' will be made during talks with Russia
SUMMARY: The Russian Embassy in Washington, D.C., did not immediately respond to CNBC's request for comment.

TITLE: Disney is hiring TikTok creators — you need to love theme parks, food and social media
SUMMARY: The job calls for social media savants who have experience in digital marketing, video editing and "an affinity for the Disney Brand."

TITLE: This Tesla owner says he mines up to $800 a month in cryptocurrency with his car
SUMMARY: Tesla owners speak to CNBC about how they've used the internal computer and battery power of the car to mine cryptocurrencies.

TITLE: How A.I. is set to evolve in 2022
SUMMARY: Areas like deep learning and large language models are set to be high on the AI research agenda this year.

TITLE: Inflation, rising rates and the Federal Reserve could whip stocks around in the week ahead
SUMMARY: The bond market could continue to set the course for stocks in the week ahead, after a choppy start to the new year.

TITLE: Elon Musk says Tesla will raise price of "Full Self-Driving" driver assistance to $12,000
SUMMARY: In a series of posts on Twitter, where he has 69.2 million followers, Musk wrote, "Tesla FSD price rising to $12k on Jan 17. Just in the US."

TITLE: Elizabeth Holmes verdict complicates upcoming trial of her ex-boyfriend and former Theranos COO Sunny Balwani
SUMMARY: Holmes was convicted on four federal fraud charges. Her ex-boyfriend, former Theranos president Ramesh Balwani, is about to go on trial on similar charges.

TITLE: Goldman-backed digital bank Starling boycotts Meta over scam ads
SUMMARY: Starling CEO Anne Boden said her firm would no longer pay for advertising on Facebook and Instagram while scammers target customers.

TITLE: Jim Cramer says these 5 'old tech' stocks could have a big year in 2022
SUMMARY: The "Mad Money" host believes Apple, Cisco, IBM, Microsoft and Oracle could post strong results in 2022.

TITLE: S&P 500 and Nasdaq fall for a fourth day on spiking rates to cap the first trading week of 2022
SUMMARY: Stocks fell on Friday at the end of a rough week for markets, which have come under pressure because of a spike in rates to begin 2022.

TITLE: Citigroup will terminate unvaccinated workers by Jan. 31, a first among Wall Street banks
SUMMARY: Citigroup has had the most aggressive vaccine policy among Wall Street firms.

TITLE: China's real estate problems are spreading even to once-healthy developers
SUMMARY: Shimao Group shares briefly plunged more than 17% Friday after Reuters reported the property developer failed to make full repayment on a trust loan.

TITLE: Saudi Arabia hires PR veteran and former Katie Couric producer for media consulting
SUMMARY: Saudi Arabia hired public relations veteran Nicolla Hewitt as a freelance media consultant.

TITLE: These European countries have a higher prevalence of Covid than both the U.S. and the U.K.
SUMMARY: Over the past 28 days, the U.S. and the U.K. have recorded the highest number of new cases of Covid-19 in the world, according to Johns Hopkins University.

TITLE: Cloud stocks are off to a brutal start to 2022 as investors sour on pandemic's top performers
SUMMARY: The Federal Reserve's move toward raising rates is pushing investors out of cloud stocks, which soared in recent years, and in search of safer assets.

TITLE: How to survive a 4-month hike: Couple that walked from Mexico to Canada shares tips with 1.7  million TikTok followers
SUMMARY: Renee Miller and Tim Beissinger hiked from Mexico to Canada during the Covid-19 pandemic,  gaining 1.7 million TikTok followers during the journey.

TITLE: Bitcoin slumps to a three-month low as cryptocurrencies extend losses
SUMMARY: Bitcoin dropped to a three-month low amid jitters over U.S. monetary policy tightening and an internet shutdown in Kazakhstan.

TITLE: Amazon cuts paid Covid leave time for workers following changes to CDC guidance
SUMMARY: Amazon will now offer one week, or up to 40 hours, paid Covid leave for all U.S. employees, instead of two weeks paid leave.

TITLE: Euro zone inflation hit a new record high of 5% in December
SUMMARY: Prices in the euro zone are continuing rise, with inflation hitting 5% in December.

TITLE: Hiring falters in December as payrolls rise only 199,000, though the unemployment rate fell to 3.9%
SUMMARY: Nonfarm payrolls were expected to increase by 422,000 in December, according to economists surveyed by Dow Jones.

TITLE: Kazakhstan president orders troops to 'fire without warning' after days of unrest
SUMMARY: Speaking in a televised address, the Kazakh president said those who failed to surrender would be "destroyed."

TITLE: Chip stocks are on the up after Samsung and STMicro issue positive updates
SUMMARY: European semiconductor stocks rose on Friday after Samsung Electronics and STMicro issued positive fourth quarter updates.

TITLE: Moderna CEO warns people may need fourth Covid shot as efficacy of boosters likely to decline over time

SUMMARY: Investors will be watching whether China's algorithm rules will affect the business models of companies like Alibaba and Tencent.

TITLE: The Federal Reserve is scaring markets with the triple threat of policy tightening
SUMMARY: Fed members are ready not only to start raising rates and tapering bond buying, but also cutting the size of the balance sheet.

TITLE: Hong Kong's Hang Seng index jumps almost 2%, leading gains in mixed Asia-Pacific trading day
SUMMARY: Markets across the globe fell sharply earlier this week since minutes from the Fed's December meeting showed officials ready to aggressively dial back policy help.

TITLE: Inflation amplifies problems for emerging markets like Kazakhstan, says analyst
SUMMARY: Rising food and fuel prices pose serious challenges for emerging economies like Kazakhstan, according to Rachel Ziemba, founder of Ziemba Insights.
